00:20:26.050 --> 00:20:28.658
-[James gasps]
-They're coming back.

279
00:20:28.701 --> 00:20:30.962
-Who?
-You know they're coming back.

280
00:20:31.006 --> 00:20:33.745
All that darkness.
you can't keep it away.

281
00:20:33.788 --> 00:20:35.962
Just-just-just
get off me. all right?

282
00:20:36.006 --> 00:20:37.050
[panting in fear]

283
00:20:40.614 --> 00:20:43.528
[phone vibrating]

284
00:20:46.745 --> 00:20:49.180
I wasn't expecting
a no-show. James.

285
00:20:49.224 --> 00:20:50.658
I'm in Silent Hill.

286
00:20:50.701 --> 00:20:51.875
[M. over phone] What?

287
00:20:51.919 --> 00:20:53.571
I did--something's
happened here.

288
00:20:53.614 --> 00:20:55.528
Something really. really bad.

289
00:20:55.571 --> 00:20:56.658
[M] James.

290
00:20:56.701 --> 00:20:58.311
Listen to me carefully.

291
00:20:58.354 --> 00:21:00.224
This is getting out of control.

292
00:21:00.267 --> 00:21:01.614
[James] I need to go home...

293
00:21:01.658 --> 00:21:03.267
to Mary.

294
00:21:03.311 --> 00:21:04.919
[M] What did you say?

295
00:21:04.962 --> 00:21:06.571
I need you to come back.

296
00:21:06.614 --> 00:21:08.311
There's no home
for you there anymore.

297
00:21:08.354 --> 00:21:09.875
[signage buzzing]

298
00:21:09.919 --> 00:21:11.224
[M] James?

299
00:21:13.354 --> 00:21:14.267
James?

300
00:21:14.311 --> 00:21:15.441
[groaning]

301
00:21:17.311 --> 00:21:20.050
[crunching footsteps]

302
00:21:21.180 --> 00:21:24.050
[signage buzzing]

303
00:21:33.311 --> 00:21:36.050
[groaning]

304
00:21:38.528 --> 00:21:41.441
[static noise from radio]

305
00:21:44.267 --> 00:21:45.658
[creature screeches]

306
00:22:01.528 --> 00:22:04.701
[club music playing on speaker]

307
00:22:04.745 --> 00:22:07.006
[Mary] I thought
you'd never come!

308
00:22:07.050 --> 00:22:10.311
-Everyone... this is James.
-Hi.

309
00:22:10.354 --> 00:22:12.267
[Claudette] So Mary tells me
you're an artist.

310
00:22:12.311 --> 00:22:13.875
[James] Yeah. Painter.

311
00:22:13.919 --> 00:22:16.137
[Claudette] And you have
the perfect muse.

312
00:22:18.050 --> 00:22:20.919
Our Mary.
she's something special.

313
00:22:20.962 --> 00:22:24.050
Sparkling little apple
of her father's eye.

314
00:22:24.093 --> 00:22:25.614
Oh. so you all know him. or...?

315
00:22:25.658 --> 00:22:26.832
[chuckling]

316
00:22:26.875 --> 00:22:28.093
Know him?

317
00:22:28.137 --> 00:22:30.441
Joshua Crane.

318
00:22:30.485 --> 00:22:33.050
Doesn't quite do it justice
when you say it out loud.

319
00:22:33.093 --> 00:22:34.701
[in unison] He changed
our lives.

320
00:22:34.745 --> 00:22:36.137
Mary's family.

321
00:22:36.180 --> 00:22:37.441
they built this town.

322
00:22:37.485 --> 00:22:39.224
Gave us purpose.

323
00:22:39.267 --> 00:22:43.354
My life was spinning out
in all directions.

324
00:22:43.398 --> 00:22:46.137
Helped me put my head
back on straight.

325
00:22:46.180 --> 00:22:48.006
I think we all
have a similar story.

326
00:22:48.050 --> 00:22:49.658
Mm.

327
00:22:49.701 --> 00:22:53.441
We have a way of seeing things
here in Silent Hill.

328
00:22:53.485 --> 00:22:55.485
But don't worry.

329
00:22:55.528 --> 00:22:57.485
I'm sure
we'll find a place for you.

330
00:23:02.006 --> 00:23:03.311
[screams outside]

331
00:23:06.267 --> 00:23:07.528
[footsteps]

332
00:23:09.311 --> 00:23:10.267
What is that?

333
00:23:11.614 --> 00:23:13.006
[flesh squelching]

334
00:23:22.006 --> 00:23:24.875
[radio crackling]

335
00:23:25.528 --> 00:23:27.137
[creature snarling]

336
00:23:28.658 --> 00:23:30.050
Who is that?!

337
00:23:32.962 --> 00:23:35.832
[sinister music]

338
00:23:38.050 --> 00:23:39.311
[creature shrieks]

339
00:23:43.267 --> 00:23:44.485
[straining effort]

340
00:23:44.528 --> 00:23:46.788
[creature screeches]

341
00:23:53.093 --> 00:23:55.745
[trembling breath]

342
00:23:55.788 --> 00:23:58.919
[tense music]

343
00:23:58.962 --> 00:24:00.311
[metallic clatter]

344
00:24:03.571 --> 00:24:05.614
[creature snarling]

345
00:24:05.658 --> 00:24:07.701
[breathing heavily]

346
00:24:09.528 --> 00:24:11.354
[static from radio]

347
00:24:11.398 --> 00:24:14.180
[Man] This is the Silent Hill
Emergency Operations System.

348
00:24:14.224 --> 00:24:16.788
This is not a test.

349
00:24:16.832 --> 00:24:19.180
City officials have issued
a health emergency

350
00:24:19.224 --> 00:24:21.701
for the city of Silent Hill
and surrounding areas.

351
00:24:21.745 --> 00:24:22.962
Residents are being ordered

352
00:24:23.006 --> 00:24:25.180
to evacuate
the area immediately.

353
00:24:27.528 --> 00:24:30.398
I repeat. this is not a test.

354
00:24:30.441 --> 00:24:32.441
What you are hearing
is not a test.

355
00:24:32.485 --> 00:24:34.701
This is the emergency
alert system.

356
00:24:34.745 --> 00:24:37.962
-Civil authorities are issuing--
-[emergency alert blaring]

357
00:24:38.006 --> 00:24:40.962
[wings flapping]

358
00:24:50.919 --> 00:24:53.832
[ground cracking]

359
00:25:10.137 --> 00:25:12.745
[low rumbling]

360
00:25:22.137 --> 00:25:24.224
[creature screeches]

361
00:25:24.267 --> 00:25:26.050
[tense music]

362
00:25:31.832 --> 00:25:35.354
[screeching]

363
00:25:44.875 --> 00:25:46.398
[footsteps clanging]

364
00:25:48.701 --> 00:25:49.788
[James groans in pain]

365
00:25:53.180 --> 00:25:54.701
[rats squeaking]

366
00:25:58.050 --> 00:26:00.919
[James grunts with effort]

367
00:26:02.614 --> 00:26:05.528
[rats squeaking]

368
00:26:13.441 --> 00:26:14.180
[pipe clanging]

369
00:26:16.571 --> 00:26:18.658
[squelching]

370
00:26:22.441 --> 00:26:24.398
[insects chittering]

371
00:26:30.485 --> 00:26:33.398
[footsteps clanging]

372
00:26:43.962 --> 00:26:46.875
[eerie shrieking]

373
00:26:51.137 --> 00:26:54.050
[tense music]

374
00:27:01.441 --> 00:27:03.180
[squeaking]

375
00:27:09.485 --> 00:27:11.050
[James grunts]

376
00:27:21.571 --> 00:27:24.528
[straining]

377
00:27:34.571 --> 00:27:37.485
[insects chittering]

378
00:27:42.788 --> 00:27:44.137
[James grunts]

379
00:27:45.658 --> 00:27:47.571
[insects chittering]

380
00:27:51.006 --> 00:27:51.788
[yells in pain]

381
00:27:56.180 --> 00:27:58.441
[panting]

382
00:27:58.485 --> 00:28:00.788
[insects bustling]

383
00:28:09.093 --> 00:28:12.006
[soft tense music]

384
00:28:17.180 --> 00:28:20.745
[panting]

385
00:28:25.788 --> 00:28:27.441
[soft squelching]

386
00:28:31.311 --> 00:28:32.701
[eerie squeal]

387
00:28:34.528 --> 00:28:36.006
[Mary. whispers] James.

388
00:28:39.311 --> 00:28:40.614
Mary?

389
00:28:43.050 --> 00:28:44.788
[soft. suspenseful music]

390
00:28:49.485 --> 00:28:51.875
Hello. handsome.

391
00:28:51.919 --> 00:28:54.267
How many times you get lost
this time around?

392
00:28:54.311 --> 00:28:55.962
I just can't believe
how much stuff I had.

393
00:28:56.006 --> 00:28:57.137
Come on. one last push.

394
00:28:57.180 --> 00:28:58.093
Mm-hmm.

395
00:28:59.093 --> 00:29:00.093
[kissing]

396
00:29:02.050 --> 00:29:03.267
Let me help you with this.

397
00:29:03.311 --> 00:29:04.701
Ooh. why thank you.

398
00:29:04.745 --> 00:29:06.224
[Mary] [chuckles softly]
You're so welcome.

399
00:29:09.311 --> 00:29:12.311
[tense music]

400
00:29:12.354 --> 00:29:15.180
[footsteps approaching]

401
00:29:41.441 --> 00:29:42.701
[door hinges squeak]

402
00:29:51.701 --> 00:29:54.745
[white noise from TV]

403
00:30:05.788 --> 00:30:08.180
[static buzzing]

404
00:30:18.614 --> 00:30:21.528
[grunting in pain]

405
00:30:24.354 --> 00:30:25.485
[screaming]

406
00:30:27.485 --> 00:30:29.093
[loud droning]

407
00:30:32.658 --> 00:30:34.180
[whimpering]

408
00:30:35.354 --> 00:30:36.745
[groaning]

409
00:30:36.788 --> 00:30:37.875
[phone ringing]

410
00:30:39.006 --> 00:30:41.267
[James panting over phone]

411
00:30:41.311 --> 00:30:42.224
Where are you?

412
00:30:44.441 --> 00:30:45.919
[groaning]
It hurts so bad. I can't...

413
00:30:45.962 --> 00:30:48.093
I can't make it stop.

414
00:30:48.137 --> 00:30:50.571
It's gonna be okay.
Just tell me where you are.

415
00:30:50.614 --> 00:30:52.050
[James] No. No.

416
00:30:52.093 --> 00:30:53.875
No. I can feel her.

417
00:30:53.919 --> 00:30:56.006
She's close.

418
00:30:56.050 --> 00:30:57.788
-I think she's--
-[phone cuts out]

419
00:30:57.832 --> 00:30:59.919
James? James?

420
00:31:01.919 --> 00:31:04.398
[panting]

421
00:31:04.441 --> 00:31:05.614
[groaning]

422
00:31:08.571 --> 00:31:10.614
[thunder rumbling]

423
00:31:10.658 --> 00:31:14.875
[heavy downpour]

424
00:31:23.311 --> 00:31:25.485
[thunder rumbling]

425
00:31:26.788 --> 00:31:30.050
[rain pattering]

426
00:31:35.962 --> 00:31:37.311
[voicemail] The mailbox
is full

427
00:31:37.354 --> 00:31:39.180
and cannot accept
any messages at this time.

428
00:31:39.224 --> 00:31:41.267
Goodbye.

429
00:31:41.311 --> 00:31:42.224
[phone thuds]

430
00:31:45.441 --> 00:31:46.919
[phone clicking]

431
00:31:51.788 --> 00:31:53.267
[Man] Hello?

432
00:31:53.311 --> 00:31:55.093
It's me.

433
00:31:55.137 --> 00:31:57.267
Yes. One of my patients
who's broken protocol.

434
00:31:57.311 --> 00:31:58.919
I need a wellness check.

435
00:31:58.962 --> 00:32:00.571
[Man] Which patient?

436
00:32:00.614 --> 00:32:02.224
James Sunderland.

437
00:32:02.267 --> 00:32:03.832
[Man] Is he a danger
to himself or anyone?

438
00:32:03.875 --> 00:32:05.875
I wouldn't say dangerous but...

439
00:32:05.919 --> 00:32:07.701
he's in trouble.

440
00:32:07.745 --> 00:32:10.875
[rain pattering]

441
00:32:10.919 --> 00:32:12.875
[metal clanks]

442
00:32:16.962 --> 00:32:18.267
[rain pattering]

443
00:32:21.267 --> 00:32:22.528
[door opens]

444
00:32:22.571 --> 00:32:23.788
[James panting]

445
00:32:33.006 --> 00:32:34.788
[wings flapping]

446
00:32:34.832 --> 00:32:36.180
[James groans]

447
00:32:39.354 --> 00:32:41.701
[James panting]

448
00:32:41.745 --> 00:32:43.180
[tense music]

449
00:33:07.354 --> 00:33:09.137
[door opens]

450
00:33:11.354 --> 00:33:13.441
-[keys thud]
-Mare?

451
00:33:16.528 --> 00:33:19.354
[distant chanting]

452
00:33:24.485 --> 00:33:26.093
We understand completely
how you feel.

453
00:33:26.137 --> 00:33:27.962
[voice echoes]

454
00:33:28.006 --> 00:33:30.441
[overlapping whispers]

455
00:33:30.485 --> 00:33:32.571
Love is not an easy thing.

456
00:33:32.614 --> 00:33:34.614
[voice echoes]

457
00:33:37.398 --> 00:33:39.354
You can get your head
all twisted around.

458
00:33:39.398 --> 00:33:40.919
You can lose yourself in it.

459
00:33:40.962 --> 00:33:43.006
[voice echoes]

460
00:33:44.528 --> 00:33:46.485
[overlapping whispers]

461
00:33:46.528 --> 00:33:48.398
But we need to stay focused.

462
00:33:49.485 --> 00:33:50.441
[door creaks]

463
00:33:50.485 --> 00:33:52.354
[whispering stops abruptly]

464
00:33:52.398 --> 00:33:55.875
And here he is.
The man of the house.

465
00:33:57.875 --> 00:33:59.962
What's going on. Jimmy boy?

466
00:34:01.137 --> 00:34:02.528
What's going on here?

467
00:34:02.571 --> 00:34:04.354
[footsteps]

468
00:34:04.398 --> 00:34:05.658
[soft tense music]

469
00:34:17.875 --> 00:34:21.398
Okay. What the fuck was that?

470
00:34:21.441 --> 00:34:23.093
I'm sorry.
They just showed up.

471
00:34:23.137 --> 00:34:24.137
Wait. they just showed up?

472
00:34:24.180 --> 00:34:25.919
Twenty people
just showed up?

473
00:34:25.962 --> 00:34:28.267
Again?
They're fucking weird. Mary.

474
00:34:28.311 --> 00:34:31.528
They're my family. James.

475
00:34:31.571 --> 00:34:33.875
They took me in
after my father died.

476
00:34:37.485 --> 00:34:38.441
All right.

477
00:34:42.745 --> 00:34:45.658
[uneasy music]

478
00:34:48.571 --> 00:34:49.832
Is that him?

479
00:34:52.398 --> 00:34:53.962
[blowing]

480
00:34:57.745 --> 00:34:59.093
[closet door closes]

481
00:34:59.137 --> 00:35:00.093
[sighs]

482
00:35:03.485 --> 00:35:05.919
Please. James...

483
00:35:05.962 --> 00:35:07.571
Please.

484
00:35:07.614 --> 00:35:09.788
I want this to be
about you and me.

485
00:35:12.137 --> 00:35:13.137
Always.

486
00:35:14.528 --> 00:35:16.354
Always just us.

487
00:35:18.788 --> 00:35:21.614
[tense music]

488
00:35:23.093 --> 00:35:25.832
[wings flapping]

489
00:35:29.614 --> 00:35:30.701
[James sighs]

490
00:35:45.311 --> 00:35:47.875
Brookhaven Hospital?

491
00:35:47.919 --> 00:35:49.224
[distant coughing]

492
00:35:50.658 --> 00:35:52.875
[gagging]

493
00:35:52.919 --> 00:35:54.658
[retching]

494
00:35:54.701 --> 00:35:56.137
[coughing]

495
00:36:02.267 --> 00:36:03.528
What the fuck?

496
00:36:03.571 --> 00:36:04.528
[James] Are you okay?

497
00:36:04.571 --> 00:36:06.614
It look like I'm okay?

498
00:36:06.658 --> 00:36:07.658
[breathing heavily]

499
00:36:07.701 --> 00:36:09.093
Who the hell are you?

500
00:36:09.137 --> 00:36:11.745
I'm-I'm James. I'm--

501
00:36:11.788 --> 00:36:14.614
Wait. why are you not sick
like everyone else?

502
00:36:14.658 --> 00:36:18.485
What? No. I'm-I'm looking
for someone.

503
00:36:18.528 --> 00:36:19.658
[Eddie] Ain't nobody here.

504
00:36:19.701 --> 00:36:20.485
[James]
No. they're at the hospital.

505
00:36:20.528 --> 00:36:22.528
[scoffs]

506
00:36:22.571 --> 00:36:24.962
[laughing]

507
00:36:25.006 --> 00:36:26.224
What's funny?

508
00:36:26.267 --> 00:36:28.180
Look around. buddy.

509
00:36:28.224 --> 00:36:29.919
Won't find anyone
at the hospital.

510
00:36:29.962 --> 00:36:32.050
City's one big cemetery.

511
00:36:34.354 --> 00:36:35.441
Oh. God.
What is happening?

512
00:36:35.485 --> 00:36:37.614
You should have seen it.

513
00:36:37.658 --> 00:36:40.224
No one could get their ass
in gear to react in time.

514
00:36:40.267 --> 00:36:41.745
Poor fucks.

515
00:36:41.788 --> 00:36:44.658
Whole town was rotten
before anyways. but this.

516
00:36:44.701 --> 00:36:46.528
this was something else.

517
00:36:46.571 --> 00:36:48.267
The fires...

518
00:36:48.311 --> 00:36:50.267
the water...

519
00:36:50.311 --> 00:36:52.398
everybody going insane.

520
00:36:52.441 --> 00:36:54.701
bleeding to death
out on the streets.

521
00:36:54.745 --> 00:36:56.614
All that crazy shit happened.

522
00:36:56.658 --> 00:36:58.267
and then these things
start to show up.

523
00:36:58.311 --> 00:37:00.398
[breathing hard]

524
00:37:02.224 --> 00:37:03.788
Wow.

525
00:37:03.832 --> 00:37:05.398
You've been lucky so far.

526
00:37:05.441 --> 00:37:06.614
What?

527
00:37:08.006 --> 00:37:09.745
Check this.

528
00:37:09.788 --> 00:37:10.875
Jesus Christ.

529
00:37:10.919 --> 00:37:13.614
[panting]

530
00:37:13.658 --> 00:37:16.701
So. what is it you do?

531
00:37:16.745 --> 00:37:18.006
What do you mean.
what do I do?

532
00:37:18.050 --> 00:37:19.006
In life. What do you do?

533
00:37:19.050 --> 00:37:20.093
I'm a--I'm a painter.

534
00:37:20.137 --> 00:37:21.658
A painter. huh?

535
00:37:21.701 --> 00:37:24.180
I ever heard of you?

536
00:37:24.224 --> 00:37:26.441
I really don't know.

537
00:37:27.701 --> 00:37:30.485
Always thought I had
the goods to be an artist.

538
00:37:30.528 --> 00:37:32.050
You ever have weird dreams?

539
00:37:35.006 --> 00:37:39.528
The shit that goes on in there.
you couldn't handle it.

540
00:37:39.571 --> 00:37:42.006
[baby screaming]

541
00:37:43.137 --> 00:37:44.398
[James] Do you hear that?

542
00:37:44.441 --> 00:37:45.701
Hear what?

543
00:37:45.745 --> 00:37:47.224
Sounds like a baby.

544
00:37:47.267 --> 00:37:48.658
A baby?

545
00:37:48.701 --> 00:37:50.050
There ain't no baby here.

546
00:37:51.180 --> 00:37:53.528
[footsteps]

547
00:37:53.571 --> 00:37:55.571
Can I ask a question?

548
00:37:56.832 --> 00:37:58.832
Why would you stay here?

549
00:37:58.875 --> 00:38:02.528
You kidding? Place is rid
of all these assholes.

550
00:38:02.571 --> 00:38:04.006
It's heaven now.

551
00:38:04.050 --> 00:38:06.919
Got the entire city to myself.

552
00:38:06.962 --> 00:38:08.006
[distant baby cooing]

553
00:38:08.050 --> 00:38:09.311
There...

554
00:38:12.701 --> 00:38:14.180
What the hell is this?

555
00:38:17.788 --> 00:38:19.224
Holy shit.

556
00:38:19.267 --> 00:38:21.137
Uh-uh. be careful.

557
00:38:21.180 --> 00:38:22.441
What are you talking about?
It's just a kid.

558
00:38:23.788 --> 00:38:27.311
Hey. what's your name?
I'm James.

559
00:38:27.354 --> 00:38:28.180
And this is--

560
00:38:28.224 --> 00:38:29.267
Eddie.

561
00:38:31.224 --> 00:38:32.398
I'm Laura.

562
00:38:32.441 --> 00:38:34.485
[James] Laura?

563
00:38:34.528 --> 00:38:36.441
Oh. you can't just stay in there
all by yourself. Laura.

564
00:38:36.485 --> 00:38:37.788
Come on. I think
you might be small enough

565
00:38:37.832 --> 00:38:38.919
to get through these bars.

566
00:38:38.962 --> 00:38:39.962
Come on.

567
00:38:40.006 --> 00:38:41.354
[Eddie] Let's get out of here.

568
00:38:41.398 --> 00:38:43.485
[James] Come on. it's okay.
You can trust me.

569
00:38:43.528 --> 00:38:45.006
You can trust me. Come on.

570
00:38:45.050 --> 00:38:46.832
I'm telling you.
this is a bad idea.

571
00:38:46.875 --> 00:38:48.267
[James] Come on. Laura.

572
00:38:48.311 --> 00:38:49.614
I got you. Come on.
We can help you.

573
00:38:52.614 --> 00:38:53.788
[loud crackle.
radio screeches]

574
00:38:55.788 --> 00:38:57.050
We need to get
our asses outta here.

575
00:38:57.093 --> 00:38:58.398
Come on. Laura.
It's all right.

576
00:38:58.441 --> 00:38:59.875
We're not gonna leave
without you. Come on.

577
00:38:59.919 --> 00:39:01.093
Just a bit closer.

578
00:39:01.137 --> 00:39:02.006
-Come on. Laura.
-[distant growling]

579
00:39:02.050 --> 00:39:03.006
-Come on.
-[Laura gasps]

580
00:39:03.050 --> 00:39:04.962
[Eddie] Jimmy. let's go!

581
00:39:05.006 --> 00:39:06.354
[James groans]

582
00:39:07.180 --> 00:39:08.528
[metal scraping]

583
00:39:11.006 --> 00:39:12.571
Would you look at that?

584
00:39:12.614 --> 00:39:15.528
You're all fucked up
like everyone else.

585
00:39:15.571 --> 00:39:16.875
[heavy footsteps]

586
00:39:18.311 --> 00:39:19.528
Get lost. kid!

587
00:39:21.701 --> 00:39:23.875
Why would you do that.
you asshole?!

588
00:39:23.919 --> 00:39:24.962
[James groans]

589
00:39:25.006 --> 00:39:26.441
[metal scraping]

590
00:39:28.093 --> 00:39:29.875
What is it you called me
again. Jimmy boy?

591
00:39:29.919 --> 00:39:31.224
An asshole?!

592
00:39:34.224 --> 00:39:35.485
Oh. shit.

593
00:39:35.528 --> 00:39:36.485
You did it. didn't ya. Jimmy?

594
00:39:37.919 --> 00:39:39.006
You woke him up.

595
00:39:44.354 --> 00:39:45.354
[panting]

596
00:39:46.528 --> 00:39:48.788
[suspenseful music]

597
00:39:53.224 --> 00:39:54.267
[Pyramid Head growling]

598
00:39:56.311 --> 00:39:57.267
[groaning in pain]

599
00:40:01.398 --> 00:40:03.224
[panting]

600
00:40:09.006 --> 00:40:10.311
[metal bending]

601
00:40:13.093 --> 00:40:14.832
[sinister music]

602
00:40:17.571 --> 00:40:19.180
[crashing]

603
00:40:19.224 --> 00:40:20.962
[sinister music continues]

604
00:40:37.658 --> 00:40:40.745
[bones crackling]

605
00:40:42.485 --> 00:40:43.614
[James] Mary?

606
00:40:56.528 --> 00:40:59.485
[music intensifies]

607
00:41:09.919 --> 00:41:13.093
[footsteps depart]

608
00:41:13.137 --> 00:41:15.919
[creature growling]

609
00:41:22.180 --> 00:41:24.528
[loud screech]

610
00:41:25.614 --> 00:41:28.614
[panting]

611
00:41:35.398 --> 00:41:36.528
[strains]

612
00:41:37.745 --> 00:41:39.832
[grunts in frustration]

613
00:41:40.832 --> 00:41:43.788
[distant growling]

614
00:41:47.180 --> 00:41:48.050
[James bangs on board]

615
00:41:56.528 --> 00:41:58.354
[spider squealing]

616
00:42:08.788 --> 00:42:10.093
[closet door closes]

617
00:42:16.398 --> 00:42:18.137
[breathing heavily]

618
00:42:21.224 --> 00:42:22.528
[spider screeches]

619
00:42:23.311 --> 00:42:25.832
[footsteps thudding]

620
00:42:27.745 --> 00:42:29.701
[thudding]

621
00:42:32.658 --> 00:42:35.614
[eerie squealing]

622
00:42:36.485 --> 00:42:37.875
[door thuds]

623
00:42:48.354 --> 00:42:50.614
[growling and groaning]

624
00:43:00.137 --> 00:43:01.267
[thudding]

625
00:43:04.311 --> 00:43:05.267
[stabs sword]

626
00:43:05.311 --> 00:43:06.180
[James gasps]

627
00:43:08.137 --> 00:43:10.875
[rapid punching]

628
00:43:14.311 --> 00:43:15.788
[tense music]

629
00:43:15.832 --> 00:43:18.745
[quavering breath]

630
00:43:18.788 --> 00:43:22.006
[suspenseful music]

631
00:43:35.701 --> 00:43:37.398
[shallow breathing]

632
00:43:39.962 --> 00:43:41.267
[Pyramid Head growls]

633
00:43:49.093 --> 00:43:51.180
[shuddering]

634
00:43:53.832 --> 00:43:56.311
[footsteps stomp]

635
00:44:03.832 --> 00:44:05.267
[emergency alarm blaring]

636
00:44:05.311 --> 00:44:08.354
[both screaming]

637
00:44:19.354 --> 00:44:21.788
[screams fade]

638
00:44:35.571 --> 00:44:38.485
[James winces]

639
00:44:47.050 --> 00:44:49.962
[breathing heavily]

640
00:45:10.311 --> 00:45:11.398
What is going on here?

641
00:45:13.398 --> 00:45:15.614
I told you not to come.

642
00:45:16.745 --> 00:45:18.701
There are secrets buried here.

643
00:45:18.745 --> 00:45:20.354
They need to stay that way.

644
00:45:20.398 --> 00:45:22.614
What secrets? What secrets?

645
00:45:24.658 --> 00:45:26.311
What you're doing...

646
00:45:28.006 --> 00:45:29.485
it won't be enough to save her.

647
00:45:29.528 --> 00:45:32.962
You can't save her. James.

648
00:45:33.006 --> 00:45:34.614
What do you mean. save her?
Save her from what?

649
00:45:34.658 --> 00:45:35.962
Stay where you are!

650
00:45:36.006 --> 00:45:37.398
Wait. wait. I'm not
trying to hurt you. I...

651
00:45:37.832 --> 00:45:39.441
Please...

652
00:45:39.485 --> 00:45:44.137
You don't know what kind of
hell you have to face.

653
00:45:44.180 --> 00:45:46.093
I didn't leave.

654
00:45:46.137 --> 00:45:47.267
None of us left!

655
00:45:49.354 --> 00:45:51.050
Don't touch me!

656
00:45:51.093 --> 00:45:52.658
No one will touch me again!

657
00:45:54.398 --> 00:45:56.180
Go.

658
00:45:56.224 --> 00:45:57.962
Just go.

659
00:46:00.962 --> 00:46:03.919
[Angela sobbing]

660
00:46:03.962 --> 00:46:06.919
[somber music]

661
00:46:10.050 --> 00:46:12.006
[running footsteps]

662
00:46:12.050 --> 00:46:14.224
[distant baby crying]

663
00:46:15.614 --> 00:46:17.354
[light buzzing]

664
00:46:22.093 --> 00:46:24.614
Shh. You don't have to cry.

665
00:46:24.658 --> 00:46:27.050
I'm right here.
You're gonna be okay.

666
00:46:27.093 --> 00:46:28.745
Hey.

667
00:46:28.788 --> 00:46:30.528
It's Laura. right?

668
00:46:33.224 --> 00:46:34.528
How did you get yourself
up there?

669
00:46:37.224 --> 00:46:38.832
He was crawling
on the ground.

670
00:46:38.875 --> 00:46:40.224
Who was?

671
00:46:40.267 --> 00:46:41.224
A monster!

672
00:46:42.832 --> 00:46:46.006
I was very scared.
But I didn't cry.

673
00:46:46.050 --> 00:46:48.267
-Catch me!
-What? [grunts]

674
00:46:50.180 --> 00:46:51.571
[breathing heavily]

675
00:46:54.788 --> 00:46:57.180
What is that?

676
00:46:57.224 --> 00:46:59.093
Show me your doll.

677
00:46:59.137 --> 00:47:01.180
Mary gave it to me.

678
00:47:01.224 --> 00:47:02.919
What?

679
00:47:02.962 --> 00:47:04.832
What did you just say?

680
00:47:04.875 --> 00:47:06.701
Who gave you the doll. Laura?

681
00:47:06.745 --> 00:47:07.875
Mary.

682
00:47:07.919 --> 00:47:10.485
Mary? Mary Crane?

683
00:47:10.528 --> 00:47:11.571
[distant clank]

684
00:47:11.614 --> 00:47:13.050
That's him!

685
00:47:13.093 --> 00:47:14.093
What?

686
00:47:14.137 --> 00:47:15.267
Hey! Laura?

687
00:47:16.571 --> 00:47:19.441
[running footsteps]

688
00:47:22.180 --> 00:47:23.441
[footsteps approaching]

689
00:47:23.485 --> 00:47:25.267
[ominous music]

690
00:47:26.962 --> 00:47:28.311
Laura. wait!

691
00:47:32.354 --> 00:47:35.093
[panting]

692
00:47:35.137 --> 00:47:36.962
[soft brooding music]

693
00:47:37.006 --> 00:47:37.962
[chuckles softly]

694
00:47:39.093 --> 00:47:40.614
Stop. please!

695
00:47:41.614 --> 00:47:42.919
[footsteps]

696
00:47:42.962 --> 00:47:45.832
[distant whispering voices]

697
00:47:48.528 --> 00:47:51.441
[tense music]

698
00:47:53.745 --> 00:47:55.745
[whispering voices continue]

699
00:47:58.224 --> 00:47:59.571
Laura?

700
00:48:01.137 --> 00:48:02.137
Laura!

701
00:48:09.267 --> 00:48:12.180
[footsteps]

702
00:48:27.267 --> 00:48:28.180
Laura?

703
00:48:33.528 --> 00:48:34.962
[Maria] I've been watching you.

704
00:48:36.701 --> 00:48:39.745
You're not from here. are you?

705
00:48:39.788 --> 00:48:41.441
I'm just looking
for this kid.

706
00:48:41.485 --> 00:48:43.050
She's all on her own.

707
00:48:44.614 --> 00:48:45.962
What?

708
00:48:48.701 --> 00:48:49.919
Are you just gonna
keep on staring.

709
00:48:49.962 --> 00:48:52.006
or are you going
to say something?

710
00:48:52.050 --> 00:48:53.093
Sorry.

711
00:48:53.137 --> 00:48:54.614
[Maria] So...

712
00:48:54.658 --> 00:48:56.267
what's your plan?

713
00:48:56.311 --> 00:48:58.267
My plan? Plan for what?

714
00:48:58.311 --> 00:48:59.832
For getting us
the hell out of this place?

715
00:48:59.875 --> 00:49:01.528
No. I'm not leaving.
I'm looking for the hospital.

716
00:49:01.571 --> 00:49:02.701
Why?

717
00:49:02.745 --> 00:49:04.398
Because my girlfriend's there.

718
00:49:04.441 --> 00:49:07.006
Everyone got sick
in Silent Hill.

719
00:49:07.050 --> 00:49:09.093
How long has your girlfriend
been in the hospital for?

720
00:49:12.528 --> 00:49:13.919
I'm-I'm not sure.

721
00:49:13.962 --> 00:49:15.050
I thought you said
she was your girlfriend.

722
00:49:16.354 --> 00:49:17.745
We've been apart.

723
00:49:17.788 --> 00:49:19.006
So. she was
your girlfriend?

724
00:49:19.050 --> 00:49:20.528
Look. I just need to find her.

725
00:49:20.571 --> 00:49:21.571
All right.

726
00:49:21.614 --> 00:49:23.137
Got it.

727
00:49:23.180 --> 00:49:24.745
Let's find her then.

728
00:49:29.745 --> 00:49:31.919
Just wanted to make sure
you were real.

729
00:49:33.267 --> 00:49:35.050
[tense music]

730
00:49:36.441 --> 00:49:38.919
I don't get it.
Why are you helping me?

731
00:49:38.962 --> 00:49:41.528
You're the first normal
person I've met in weeks.

732
00:49:41.571 --> 00:49:43.050
Strength in numbers.

733
00:49:44.614 --> 00:49:46.485
You don't look like
you've been here weeks.

734
00:49:46.528 --> 00:49:47.962
[Maria] Why. thank you.

735
00:49:48.006 --> 00:49:50.137
You. on the other hand...

736
00:49:50.180 --> 00:49:51.919
[James] What?

737
00:49:51.962 --> 00:49:54.658
You look fucked.

738
00:49:54.701 --> 00:49:56.050
[scoffs]

739
00:49:56.093 --> 00:49:57.875
[footsteps]

740
00:49:57.919 --> 00:49:59.875
-[radio screeches]
-Shit. Come on.

741
00:49:59.919 --> 00:50:01.528
-What?
-Every time this thing goes off.

742
00:50:01.571 --> 00:50:02.658
something's getting close.

743
00:50:02.701 --> 00:50:04.180
-Come on.
-What?

744
00:50:04.224 --> 00:50:06.832
Shit. Come on.
Quick. this way.

745
00:50:06.875 --> 00:50:08.701
[creature screeching]

746
00:50:10.962 --> 00:50:12.745
Shh. Hide. hide. hide.

747
00:50:14.485 --> 00:50:16.788
[suspenseful music]

748
00:50:20.919 --> 00:50:22.528
[squelching]

749
00:50:25.006 --> 00:50:26.267
[both shuddering]

750
00:50:28.919 --> 00:50:31.832
[acid melting]

751
00:50:48.354 --> 00:50:51.224
[pensive music]

752
00:51:05.832 --> 00:51:07.614
[muted chatter]

753
00:51:13.875 --> 00:51:16.093
[indistinct conversation]

754
00:51:32.137 --> 00:51:35.224
[suspenseful music]

755
00:51:49.962 --> 00:51:52.919
[tense music]

756
00:51:58.006 --> 00:51:59.788
[gate rattles]

757
00:52:02.788 --> 00:52:03.919
[poster tearing]

758
00:52:11.311 --> 00:52:12.485
[gate clanks]

759
00:52:15.180 --> 00:52:16.485
[James panting]

760
00:52:23.441 --> 00:52:25.093
[footsteps]

761
00:52:31.006 --> 00:52:32.701
[gate rattling. clanks]

762
00:52:47.614 --> 00:52:49.398
[trash can sliding]

763
00:52:55.614 --> 00:52:57.398
[hissing]

764
00:53:10.788 --> 00:53:12.571
[iron door rumbling]

765
00:53:18.745 --> 00:53:21.745
[footsteps]

766
00:53:21.788 --> 00:53:23.658
[water dripping]

767
00:53:42.528 --> 00:53:45.528
[distant voices chanting]

768
00:53:46.658 --> 00:53:48.137
[Maria] James!

769
00:53:48.180 --> 00:53:50.050
Hey. hey. You all right?

770
00:53:50.093 --> 00:53:51.962
Yeah. yeah.

771
00:53:52.006 --> 00:53:53.441
We need to go.

772
00:53:53.485 --> 00:53:54.745
The hospital's close.

773
00:53:56.485 --> 00:53:59.137
[soft. tense music]

774
00:54:09.137 --> 00:54:10.354
[metal clanks]

775
00:54:27.919 --> 00:54:29.006
[keyboard tapping]

776
00:54:29.050 --> 00:54:30.788
[James] Everything's dead.

777
00:54:33.788 --> 00:54:34.658
[folder thuds]

778
00:54:38.050 --> 00:54:39.919
So. walk me through this.

779
00:54:39.962 --> 00:54:42.788
You're looking for your
kind-of girlfriend.

780
00:54:42.832 --> 00:54:44.180
That's right.

781
00:54:45.962 --> 00:54:47.875
And how long has it been
since you've seen her?

782
00:54:49.832 --> 00:54:51.962
I'm not sure.

783
00:54:52.006 --> 00:54:54.398
And we're sure
she's still your girlfriend?

784
00:54:56.962 --> 00:54:58.788
What?

785
00:54:58.832 --> 00:55:01.528
A girl can get into
a lot of trouble in this town.

786
00:55:01.571 --> 00:55:02.614
Where are you going?

787
00:55:02.658 --> 00:55:04.614
Need to stretch my legs.

788
00:55:04.658 --> 00:55:06.267
[receding footsteps]

789
00:55:14.788 --> 00:55:16.485
Toxicology unit.

790
00:55:18.614 --> 00:55:20.224
I think I found her.

791
00:55:20.267 --> 00:55:21.311
[Doctor. on tape]
Patient admitted at noon

792
00:55:21.354 --> 00:55:23.354
after collapsing in the street.

793
00:55:23.398 --> 00:55:25.788
On admission. she presented
with severe anemia.

794
00:55:25.832 --> 00:55:27.528
high-grade fever.
and significant

795
00:55:27.571 --> 00:55:29.962
subconjunctival
and nasal hemorrhaging.

796
00:55:30.006 --> 00:55:32.875
Initial blood work revealed
critically low platelet levels.

797
00:55:32.919 --> 00:55:35.962
likely due to exposure
to an unidentified substance.

798
00:55:36.006 --> 00:55:37.571
Fever since resolved.

799
00:55:37.614 --> 00:55:40.050
patient remains stable
but physically weakened.

800
00:55:41.354 --> 00:55:43.267
Miss.
do you remember your name?

801
00:55:44.701 --> 00:55:46.267
[Mary. on tape] Mary.

802
00:55:46.311 --> 00:55:47.745
Mary Crane.

803
00:55:47.788 --> 00:55:48.832
[recorder clicks]

804
00:55:50.050 --> 00:55:51.050
There were rumors.

805
00:55:54.528 --> 00:55:56.354
There was this
religious group.

806
00:55:56.398 --> 00:55:59.528
old-school
Silent Hill crazies.

807
00:55:59.571 --> 00:56:03.180
Founded by this preacher
named Joshua Crane.

808
00:56:03.224 --> 00:56:05.701
Even after he died.
they used to worship him

809
00:56:05.745 --> 00:56:09.050
as some kind of prophet or God.

810
00:56:09.875 --> 00:56:12.875
And his daughter.
they would...

811
00:56:12.919 --> 00:56:14.224
Wait.

812
00:56:14.267 --> 00:56:16.006
She's who you're looking for.
isn't she?

813
00:56:22.311 --> 00:56:24.571
[distant voices chanting]

814
00:56:26.398 --> 00:56:28.224
[Doctor. on tape]
Miss Crane.

815
00:56:28.267 --> 00:56:30.658
this drug that they've been
giving you all these years...

816
00:56:32.311 --> 00:56:34.093
[soft. suspenseful music]

817
00:56:36.398 --> 00:56:37.832
[Mary. on tape]
It made me feel whole.

818
00:56:39.919 --> 00:56:41.875
It made me feel part of them.

819
00:56:43.441 --> 00:56:45.093
[breath shuddering]

820
00:56:46.180 --> 00:56:48.485
[crowd chanting]

821
00:56:48.528 --> 00:56:50.006
[shouts] Mary?!

822
00:56:50.050 --> 00:56:52.093
[Doctor. on tape]
It's killed your free will.

823
00:56:53.006 --> 00:56:55.267
[distant singing]

824
00:56:55.311 --> 00:56:57.658
[shouts] Mary!

825
00:56:57.701 --> 00:56:58.962
[Doctor. on tape]
And it's caused permanent damage

826
00:56:59.006 --> 00:57:00.093
to your body.

827
00:57:02.050 --> 00:57:03.658
[shouting] Leave her alone!

828
00:57:05.224 --> 00:57:06.614
[Mary. on tape]
They loved me.

829
00:57:06.658 --> 00:57:08.701
I thought they did.

830
00:57:08.745 --> 00:57:11.398
[crowd] What was his
is now ours.

831
00:57:13.006 --> 00:57:15.311
-[James] Mary!
-What was his is now ours.

832
00:57:18.571 --> 00:57:19.701
[sobbing]

833
00:57:22.050 --> 00:57:23.180
[Mary. on tape] My blood.

834
00:57:25.832 --> 00:57:27.354
[white noise on TV]

835
00:57:30.875 --> 00:57:33.571
[Mary. on tape]
All this blood wasn't mine?

836
00:57:34.962 --> 00:57:36.398
[emergency alarm blaring]

837
00:57:36.441 --> 00:57:38.093
[groaning]

838
00:57:42.137 --> 00:57:44.398
[ground crackling]

839
00:57:51.354 --> 00:57:53.658
[alarm continues]

840
00:57:56.311 --> 00:57:58.093
[crackling]

841
00:58:04.614 --> 00:58:06.050
-[blood splashes]
-[Maria] Let's go!

842
00:58:07.180 --> 00:58:08.614
-[James] What?
-[Maria] Go!

843
00:58:10.441 --> 00:58:11.875
[groaning]

844
00:58:16.788 --> 00:58:19.485
[both panting]

845
00:58:19.528 --> 00:58:22.050
[distant classical music
playing]

846
00:58:25.528 --> 00:58:26.875
[walls crackling]

847
00:58:28.528 --> 00:58:30.050
We've gotta find her.

848
00:58:30.093 --> 00:58:31.701
Now.

849
00:58:31.745 --> 00:58:32.919
[strains]

850
00:58:32.962 --> 00:58:34.006
Come on.

851
00:58:35.137 --> 00:58:38.180
[footsteps thudding]

852
00:58:39.311 --> 00:58:41.788
[both panting]

853
00:58:46.311 --> 00:58:47.745
[door opens]

854
00:58:53.528 --> 00:58:56.180
[dark. suspenseful music]

855
00:59:03.311 --> 00:59:06.180
[rhythmic metal clanking]

856
00:59:09.441 --> 00:59:11.050
[bones cracking]

857
00:59:24.093 --> 00:59:25.528
Come on!

858
00:59:25.571 --> 00:59:26.745
[door opens. squeaks]

859
00:59:27.745 --> 00:59:28.875
[monsters moaning]

860
00:59:30.832 --> 00:59:32.354
[both panting]

861
00:59:34.137 --> 00:59:36.701
[creatures squealing]

862
00:59:40.441 --> 00:59:42.528
[screaming]

863
00:59:45.788 --> 00:59:47.137
[elevator clicking]

864
00:59:47.180 --> 00:59:48.398
Come on. come on.

865
00:59:49.528 --> 00:59:51.571
[skull thuds. crashes]

866
00:59:51.614 --> 00:59:53.614
Here.

867
00:59:53.658 --> 00:59:55.441
[elevator clicking]

868
00:59:55.485 --> 00:59:56.701
[creatures growling. screeching]

869
00:59:57.832 --> 00:59:59.919
[both shuddering]

870
00:59:59.962 --> 01:00:01.224
[growling]

871
01:00:09.571 --> 01:00:11.919
[James grunts]

872
01:00:15.311 --> 01:00:16.832
[shuddering]

873
01:00:21.745 --> 01:00:22.745
James!

874
01:00:22.788 --> 01:00:23.832
[groans]

875
01:00:24.745 --> 01:00:25.701
[grunts]

876
01:00:25.745 --> 01:00:26.875
[strains]

877
01:00:26.919 --> 01:00:27.832
[elevator pings]

878
01:00:35.441 --> 01:00:37.050
[screaming]

879
01:00:39.875 --> 01:00:42.614
[elevator whirring]

880
01:00:45.050 --> 01:00:46.398
[breathing heavily]

881
01:00:46.441 --> 01:00:47.658
[whispers] Help.

882
01:00:50.006 --> 01:00:51.137
Here. Let me see.

883
01:00:52.832 --> 01:00:54.832
-[blood splatters]
-Oh. no.

884
01:00:55.962 --> 01:00:58.050
[groans in pain]

885
01:01:03.441 --> 01:01:05.398
[straining]

886
01:01:05.441 --> 01:01:06.962
[grunting]

887
01:01:08.354 --> 01:01:09.485
[effort grunts]

888
01:01:10.788 --> 01:01:12.224
[Maria groaning]

889
01:01:19.745 --> 01:01:21.658
[breathing heavily]

890
01:01:24.919 --> 01:01:26.311
[James groans]

891
01:01:36.528 --> 01:01:38.180
[doors squeak]

892
01:01:41.485 --> 01:01:44.137
[panting]

893
01:01:46.441 --> 01:01:49.832
-[squelching]
-[gasps. groaning]

894
01:01:55.180 --> 01:01:57.180
You can say it.

895
01:01:57.224 --> 01:01:58.962
What?

896
01:02:00.006 --> 01:02:01.485
I look just like her.

897
01:02:04.267 --> 01:02:07.441
No. No. no. no.
How would you know that?

898
01:02:07.485 --> 01:02:09.788
It's how you look at me.

899
01:02:09.832 --> 01:02:12.485
[breathing deeply]

900
01:02:12.528 --> 01:02:16.614
Look. I'm gonna go upstairs.
I want you to stay here.

901
01:02:16.658 --> 01:02:18.354
[grunts]
No. don't leave me.

902
01:02:18.398 --> 01:02:19.875
You'll be safer here.

903
01:02:19.919 --> 01:02:21.485
I'm gonna look for Mary.
and I'll come right back.

904
01:02:21.528 --> 01:02:23.962
Promise me something.

905
01:02:24.006 --> 01:02:26.571
If you find out she's gone.
we leave.

906
01:02:26.614 --> 01:02:28.006
Together.

907
01:02:28.050 --> 01:02:29.745
We don't look back.

908
01:02:36.962 --> 01:02:38.398
[strains with effort]

909
01:02:43.919 --> 01:02:45.050
[Laura] Who is she?

910
01:02:50.050 --> 01:02:51.398
Just someone
I'm trying to help.

911
01:02:54.224 --> 01:03:00.398
Now. Laura. you have
to tell me where Mary is.

912
01:03:00.441 --> 01:03:02.093
Doesn't look like
you want to find her.

913
01:03:02.137 --> 01:03:05.832
No. I do.
It's all I want.

914
01:03:05.875 --> 01:03:09.311
Now. please. where is she?

915
01:03:09.354 --> 01:03:10.571
My baby's sad!

916
01:03:10.614 --> 01:03:13.485
[doll crying]

917
01:03:19.485 --> 01:03:22.571
He's cold and sad.

918
01:03:22.614 --> 01:03:25.137
Sad because nobody loved him.

919
01:03:25.180 --> 01:03:27.311
Just like Mary.

920
01:03:27.354 --> 01:03:28.658
What?

921
01:03:29.354 --> 01:03:31.267
You left her all...

922
01:03:31.311 --> 01:03:32.832
[shrieks] ...alone!

923
01:03:34.919 --> 01:03:37.224
-Ah!
-[high-pitched ringing]

924
01:03:37.267 --> 01:03:39.485
You have to get to her
before it's too late.

925
01:03:44.137 --> 01:03:45.962
No. wait! Laura!

926
01:03:47.441 --> 01:03:48.441
Laura!

927
01:03:52.224 --> 01:03:54.875
[footsteps thudding on stairs]

928
01:04:07.832 --> 01:04:10.137
Why are you doing this?

929
01:04:10.180 --> 01:04:11.614
No one said
it would be easy.

930
01:04:13.006 --> 01:04:15.745
[door opens. squeaks]

931
01:04:20.441 --> 01:04:22.701
[panting]

932
01:04:22.745 --> 01:04:24.137
No.

933
01:04:27.354 --> 01:04:28.788
[door opens. squeaks]

934
01:04:30.267 --> 01:04:32.311
What?

935
01:04:32.354 --> 01:04:33.658
Laura?

936
01:04:36.137 --> 01:04:37.354
[giggles]

937
01:04:37.398 --> 01:04:39.180
-Laura?!
-[door closes]

938
01:04:40.398 --> 01:04:41.614
Laura?!

939
01:04:41.658 --> 01:04:43.093
Laura. open the door!

940
01:04:45.093 --> 01:04:47.701
-[banging on door]
-Open the door!

941
01:04:47.745 --> 01:04:50.745
[strange growls]

942
01:05:14.571 --> 01:05:15.614
[loud shrieks]

943
01:05:15.658 --> 01:05:17.050
[hospital bed sliding]

944
01:05:25.267 --> 01:05:28.137
[bed clanking]

945
01:05:31.137 --> 01:05:32.658
[Laura] Why'd you come. James?

946
01:05:38.050 --> 01:05:39.919
What did you think you'd find?

947
01:05:57.267 --> 01:05:58.441
[blood drips]

948
01:05:59.788 --> 01:06:00.962
[James] Mary.

949
01:06:17.398 --> 01:06:18.267
[pipe clanks to floor]

950
01:06:18.311 --> 01:06:21.311
[James choking]

951
01:06:22.788 --> 01:06:25.832
[Laura] Come back
when you're ready. James.

952
01:06:25.875 --> 01:06:28.267
-[choking]
-[Doctor] Mr. Sunderland?

953
01:06:28.311 --> 01:06:30.614
Mr. Sunderland?

954
01:06:30.658 --> 01:06:32.354
Are you with us. Mr. Sunderland?

955
01:06:32.398 --> 01:06:34.093
[heart monitor beeping]

956
01:06:34.137 --> 01:06:35.745
What?

957
01:06:35.788 --> 01:06:36.919
What's going on?

958
01:06:36.962 --> 01:06:38.701
What's going on?
Where am I?

959
01:06:38.745 --> 01:06:40.050
Where am I?

960
01:06:40.093 --> 01:06:41.441
Brookhaven Hospital.

961
01:06:41.485 --> 01:06:42.528
Silent Hill.

962
01:06:44.006 --> 01:06:46.093
Where is she?

963
01:06:46.137 --> 01:06:47.311
Where is she?

964
01:06:47.354 --> 01:06:48.398
Where is who?

965
01:06:48.441 --> 01:06:49.919
Mary. Mary Crane.

966
01:06:49.962 --> 01:06:51.441
[footsteps approaching]

967
01:06:53.224 --> 01:06:54.224
What?

968
01:06:58.180 --> 01:07:00.571
Hello. James.

969
01:07:00.614 --> 01:07:04.050
I know where she is.
[breathes heavily]

970
01:07:06.528 --> 01:07:09.311
You need to let go of her.

971
01:07:09.354 --> 01:07:10.528
She's gone.

972
01:07:12.614 --> 01:07:14.528
She's dead. James.

973
01:07:17.398 --> 01:07:19.919
She's been dead
for months now.

974
01:07:19.962 --> 01:07:21.614
You know that.

975
01:07:26.354 --> 01:07:29.093
Why would you say that?

976
01:07:29.137 --> 01:07:32.224
[eerie ambient music]

977
01:07:32.267 --> 01:07:33.745
[M] We've got a lot
of serious work to do.

978
01:07:35.137 --> 01:07:36.354
But we'll get you through it.

979
01:07:38.093 --> 01:07:40.093
You just have to
promise me something.

980
01:07:43.875 --> 01:07:45.528
You need to want to
see yourself get better

981
01:07:45.571 --> 01:07:47.093
as much as I do.

982
01:08:00.658 --> 01:08:03.571
[emotional music]

983
01:08:09.180 --> 01:08:12.180
[car approaching]

984
01:08:33.137 --> 01:08:34.267
[door opens]

985
01:08:42.485 --> 01:08:44.050
[Mary] Why are you
sitting in the dark?

986
01:08:45.311 --> 01:08:47.050
[suitcase slides]

987
01:08:47.093 --> 01:08:48.788
Pack your things.

988
01:08:48.832 --> 01:08:51.658
I want us out of here.

989
01:08:51.701 --> 01:08:53.137
Why are you acting like this?

990
01:08:55.354 --> 01:08:56.788
[James] Guess what I did today.

991
01:08:58.919 --> 01:09:01.006
I saw this girl
across the street...

992
01:09:03.180 --> 01:09:04.701
so I followed her.

993
01:09:04.745 --> 01:09:06.354
[Mary] Stop.

994
01:09:06.398 --> 01:09:08.441
I went down this long
flight of stairs.

995
01:09:08.485 --> 01:09:10.006
[Mary] Stop.

996
01:09:10.050 --> 01:09:12.788
And I saw these monsters.

997
01:09:12.832 --> 01:09:14.658
I saw them tear her apart.

998
01:09:14.701 --> 01:09:16.962
-Just stop!
-[glass shatters]

999
01:09:21.614 --> 01:09:23.571
How long?

1000
01:09:23.614 --> 01:09:25.180
Since I was a girl.

1001
01:09:27.745 --> 01:09:30.614
Why would your father
do this to you?

1002
01:09:30.658 --> 01:09:32.006
I don't know.

1003
01:09:33.528 --> 01:09:35.050
I never had a choice.

1004
01:09:37.528 --> 01:09:39.224
This is your last chance.

1005
01:09:41.006 --> 01:09:43.093
Walk out that door with me now.

1006
01:09:43.137 --> 01:09:44.485
Not when you're like this.

1007
01:09:44.528 --> 01:09:46.745
What am I like?

1008
01:09:46.788 --> 01:09:48.745
Scared.

1009
01:09:48.788 --> 01:09:50.832
You think I'm scared?

1010
01:09:50.875 --> 01:09:52.832
[raises voice]
I am not scared!

1011
01:09:52.875 --> 01:09:55.485
I am not scared of any of you!

1012
01:09:55.528 --> 01:09:57.919
[Mary whimpers]

1013
01:09:57.962 --> 01:10:00.180
But you're disgusted.

1014
01:10:00.224 --> 01:10:02.614
Say it.

1015
01:10:02.658 --> 01:10:05.571
Say I'm disgusting to you.
Say it!

1016
01:10:07.137 --> 01:10:11.180
That day. I was leaving.

1017
01:10:11.224 --> 01:10:13.962
I was leaving.
and then you showed up.

1018
01:10:16.701 --> 01:10:19.224
Why-why didn't you
just tell me?

1019
01:10:19.267 --> 01:10:21.485
Because I knew you'd walk away.

1020
01:10:23.745 --> 01:10:26.006
I see the way
you're looking at me.

1021
01:10:26.050 --> 01:10:29.006
That'll never change now.

1022
01:10:29.050 --> 01:10:33.701
I told you there were things.
You-you promised me.

1023
01:10:33.745 --> 01:10:36.528
[emotional music]

1024
01:10:41.528 --> 01:10:43.701
[footsteps receding]

1025
01:10:54.571 --> 01:10:55.832
[car alarm beeps]

1026
01:10:58.962 --> 01:11:00.311
[car door opens]

1027
01:11:22.485 --> 01:11:23.224
[car door shuts]

1028
01:11:29.180 --> 01:11:31.267
[Doctor] How is he today?

1029
01:11:31.311 --> 01:11:32.658
[M] Calm. I guess.

1030
01:11:34.224 --> 01:11:38.571
I've worked with vets.
all kinds of trauma.

1031
01:11:38.614 --> 01:11:42.224
but this is different.
He won't let me in at all.

1032
01:11:42.267 --> 01:11:44.398
How long have you been
treating him?

1033
01:11:44.441 --> 01:11:45.832
Almost a year.

1034
01:11:47.311 --> 01:11:49.528
But it's gotten worse.

1035
01:11:49.571 --> 01:11:53.658
That woman. Mary.
she was everything to him.

1036
01:11:54.311 --> 01:11:55.745
Since her lost her.

1037
01:11:55.788 --> 01:11:57.962
it's like he lost
his grip on reality.

1038
01:11:58.006 --> 01:12:00.441
and his desire to regain it.

1039
01:12:03.398 --> 01:12:05.137
Mary died after their breakup.

1040
01:12:06.528 --> 01:12:08.614
And he just won't accept it.

1041
01:12:08.658 --> 01:12:11.701
[birds chirping]

1042
01:12:11.745 --> 01:12:14.571
[emotional music playing]

1043
01:12:18.006 --> 01:12:20.006
It's good to see you up. James.

1044
01:12:21.571 --> 01:12:23.485
How are you feeling today?

1045
01:12:26.354 --> 01:12:27.788
James?

1046
01:12:32.485 --> 01:12:34.224
I just wish...

1047
01:12:35.875 --> 01:12:38.050
I wish I hadn't let her down.

1048
01:12:41.788 --> 01:12:43.919
You're blaming yourself. but...

1049
01:12:46.267 --> 01:12:48.962
all this chaos in your mind...

1050
01:12:49.006 --> 01:12:51.093
it's not real.

1051
01:12:52.485 --> 01:12:56.745
It’s not real.
and it almost destroyed you.

1052
01:12:58.224 --> 01:13:00.658
We can still fix this.

1053
01:13:00.701 --> 01:13:02.832
But it's got to be
your decision.

1054
01:13:07.962 --> 01:13:11.788
Thank you.
For everything.

1055
01:13:16.006 --> 01:13:18.919
[footsteps receding]

1056
01:13:30.962 --> 01:13:33.832
[tense. sinister music]

1057
01:13:39.137 --> 01:13:42.137
[wings flapping]

1058
01:13:42.180 --> 01:13:47.137
[emergency alarm blaring]

1059
01:13:54.006 --> 01:13:56.919
[walls crackling]

1060
01:14:06.832 --> 01:14:08.614
[Maria] You didn't find her?

1061
01:14:13.658 --> 01:14:17.050
Then we can leave.
Together.

1062
01:14:19.137 --> 01:14:21.311
[groans]

1063
01:14:21.354 --> 01:14:24.006
You promised. James.

1064
01:14:27.050 --> 01:14:29.962
[emotional music playing]

1065
01:14:31.311 --> 01:14:33.658
You look just like her.

1066
01:14:35.745 --> 01:14:37.919
I never told you my name.

1067
01:14:41.788 --> 01:14:43.485
It's Maria.

1068
01:14:47.311 --> 01:14:49.614
[kissing]

1069
01:14:57.354 --> 01:14:59.875
Or we can stay here together...

1070
01:14:59.919 --> 01:15:02.093
if you want.

1071
01:15:02.137 --> 01:15:03.745
Just us.

1072
01:15:11.311 --> 01:15:12.398
What is it?

1073
01:15:14.701 --> 01:15:17.180
Where are you going?

1074
01:15:17.224 --> 01:15:19.180
[breathing heavily]

1075
01:15:22.571 --> 01:15:24.093
James.

1076
01:15:24.137 --> 01:15:25.311
Wait for me.

1077
01:15:27.354 --> 01:15:28.832
You won't find her down there.

1078
01:15:30.919 --> 01:15:32.571
[elevator clanks]

1079
01:15:34.006 --> 01:15:35.050
[elevator pings]

1080
01:15:37.658 --> 01:15:39.006
Please.

1081
01:15:44.832 --> 01:15:47.745
[elevator door closing]

1082
01:15:51.788 --> 01:15:53.267
[elevator pings]

1083
01:15:54.398 --> 01:15:56.962
[elevator in free fall]

1084
01:15:57.006 --> 01:15:58.745
Why are you doing this?

1085
01:15:58.788 --> 01:16:00.658
[tense music playing]

1086
01:16:04.528 --> 01:16:06.658
You were free of all this pain.

1087
01:16:11.441 --> 01:16:12.658
James!

1088
01:16:18.962 --> 01:16:20.093
James!

1089
01:16:21.441 --> 01:16:22.398
James!

1090
01:16:24.398 --> 01:16:25.658
James!

1091
01:16:25.701 --> 01:16:27.180
[elevator powering down]

1092
01:16:32.485 --> 01:16:33.832
[elevator door opening]

1093
01:16:36.701 --> 01:16:38.050
You can't go in there.

1094
01:16:56.614 --> 01:16:58.006
Let's go back.

1095
01:17:00.180 --> 01:17:01.745
We can still go back.

1096
01:17:05.875 --> 01:17:08.050
Please don't go any further.

1097
01:17:26.701 --> 01:17:28.658
It's over
if you want it to be.

1098
01:17:34.614 --> 01:17:36.398
Mary's not dead.

1099
01:17:37.962 --> 01:17:39.180
Not to me.

1100
01:17:41.311 --> 01:17:42.832
And you're not real.

1101
01:17:44.485 --> 01:17:46.354
You're just in my way.

1102
01:17:46.398 --> 01:17:47.832
No.

1103
01:17:47.875 --> 01:17:50.006
No. no.
No. no. no. no. no.

1104
01:17:50.050 --> 01:17:51.311
Look at me. James.

1105
01:17:54.267 --> 01:17:56.354
Goodbye. Maria.

1106
01:17:56.398 --> 01:17:57.919
[lights flickering. clanking]

1107
01:18:00.485 --> 01:18:02.311
[screams in pain]

1108
01:18:04.485 --> 01:18:06.832
[wet squelching]

1109
01:18:10.658 --> 01:18:12.398
[blood spurting]

1110
01:18:37.701 --> 01:18:40.571
[rhythmic heavy clanking]

1111
01:19:00.267 --> 01:19:01.137
[bottle clanks]

1112
01:19:11.962 --> 01:19:13.224
[James groans]

1113
01:19:15.354 --> 01:19:18.180
[water splashes.
blooping softly]

1114
01:19:38.006 --> 01:19:40.919
[gasping for air]

1115
01:19:44.614 --> 01:19:46.311
[breathing heavily]

1116
01:19:51.137 --> 01:19:54.050
[flames roaring]

1117
01:20:10.614 --> 01:20:13.267
[roaring fire]

1118
01:20:16.745 --> 01:20:19.528
[flames roaring]

1119
01:20:22.485 --> 01:20:24.006
[distant thud]

1120
01:20:33.224 --> 01:20:34.528
[Laura] You're finally here.

1121
01:20:36.441 --> 01:20:37.745
Laura?

1122
01:20:37.788 --> 01:20:38.571
[Laura giggles]

1123
01:20:41.441 --> 01:20:44.571
[soft music playing]

1124
01:20:44.614 --> 01:20:46.571
[giggles]

1125
01:20:49.398 --> 01:20:51.093
[James] I'm not playing
anymore. Laura.

1126
01:20:53.354 --> 01:20:54.962
Do you think
you're ready to face it?

1127
01:21:00.137 --> 01:21:02.701
Do you think
you're ready to face us?

1128
01:21:02.745 --> 01:21:03.919
[shuddering]

1129
01:21:08.006 --> 01:21:09.962
[doll cooing]

1130
01:21:15.441 --> 01:21:17.658
[James] Why are you
doing this to me?

1131
01:21:17.701 --> 01:21:19.311
To help you remember.

1132
01:21:21.354 --> 01:21:23.050
What's her name?

1133
01:21:23.093 --> 01:21:24.441
What?

1134
01:21:24.485 --> 01:21:25.398
Think. James.

1135
01:21:25.441 --> 01:21:26.267
[groans]

1136
01:21:29.006 --> 01:21:30.354
What's Mary's full name?

1137
01:21:32.962 --> 01:21:34.919
[groans]

1138
01:21:34.962 --> 01:21:36.745
Our full name. James...

1139
01:21:37.962 --> 01:21:39.398
[groans]

1140
01:21:44.962 --> 01:21:47.614
[breathing heavily]

1141
01:21:47.658 --> 01:21:49.006
[Laura] It's time now.

1142
01:21:51.137 --> 01:21:52.875
[flames crackling]

1143
01:21:55.745 --> 01:21:58.788
And now.
there's nothing left to hide.

1144
01:22:01.224 --> 01:22:02.571
[flames crackling]

1145
01:22:10.962 --> 01:22:12.137
[door closes]

1146
01:22:12.180 --> 01:22:14.441
[eerie ambient music]

1147
01:22:14.485 --> 01:22:16.398
[Angela sobbing]

1148
01:22:25.354 --> 01:22:27.441
Haven't you had enough?

1149
01:22:27.485 --> 01:22:28.832
Disgusting.

1150
01:22:28.875 --> 01:22:30.267
You're disgusting!

1151
01:22:33.311 --> 01:22:35.354
You--you see.

1152
01:22:35.398 --> 01:22:37.354
Please tell me
you can see it.

1153
01:22:41.050 --> 01:22:43.267
I can't get away from him.

1154
01:22:43.311 --> 01:22:47.050
He'll never stop hurting me.

1155
01:22:47.093 --> 01:22:49.311
Let me help you.

1156
01:22:49.354 --> 01:22:50.832
Don't! Don't.

1157
01:22:50.875 --> 01:22:52.224
Stay away.

1158
01:22:52.267 --> 01:22:54.137
[sobbing]

1159
01:22:55.658 --> 01:22:56.658
Please.

1160
01:23:00.745 --> 01:23:01.832
[grunts]

1161
01:23:20.832 --> 01:23:22.788
[growling softly]

1162
01:23:32.485 --> 01:23:34.441
[James breathing heavily]

1163
01:23:40.614 --> 01:23:42.267
[tense music]

1164
01:23:44.311 --> 01:23:45.701
[growling softy]

1165
01:23:47.962 --> 01:23:49.267
[James] Mary?

1166
01:23:49.311 --> 01:23:50.571
[growling]

1167
01:24:11.832 --> 01:24:12.962
[whispers] I'm sorry.

1168
01:24:14.398 --> 01:24:15.571
[squeals]

1169
01:24:30.571 --> 01:24:33.441
-[door opens]
-[fire roaring]

1170
01:24:40.788 --> 01:24:42.267
Mary?!

1171
01:24:45.962 --> 01:24:47.658
No. wait!

1172
01:24:47.701 --> 01:24:49.050
[running footsteps]

1173
01:24:52.267 --> 01:24:53.614
[door opens]

1174
01:25:01.441 --> 01:25:04.311
[fire crackling]

1175
01:25:33.571 --> 01:25:36.311
[music playing on radio]

1176
01:25:43.528 --> 01:25:45.180
[M] You need to let go of her.

1177
01:25:47.614 --> 01:25:48.962
She's gone.

1178
01:25:50.962 --> 01:25:52.745
She's dead. James.

1179
01:25:55.614 --> 01:25:58.137
She's been dead for months now.

1180
01:25:58.180 --> 01:25:59.745
You know that.

1181
01:26:06.614 --> 01:26:08.788
[birds chirping]

1182
01:26:25.441 --> 01:26:27.050
[Mary] You came.

1183
01:26:27.093 --> 01:26:28.180
[James] Of course.

1184
01:26:30.267 --> 01:26:31.485
As soon as I could.

1185
01:26:31.528 --> 01:26:33.701
[Mary] It's okay.

1186
01:26:33.745 --> 01:26:35.832
I never should have left.

1187
01:26:35.875 --> 01:26:38.398
[Mary] Whether you would've
stayed or not.

1188
01:26:38.441 --> 01:26:41.267
I still would've gotten sick.

1189
01:26:41.311 --> 01:26:43.398
[James] Well. maybe
I could've helped.

1190
01:26:43.441 --> 01:26:44.788
No one could've.

1191
01:26:46.224 --> 01:26:48.180
My father poisoned me.

1192
01:26:49.875 --> 01:26:52.006
He poisoned me my whole life.

1193
01:26:55.962 --> 01:26:58.050
I tried to shield you from it.

1194
01:26:59.354 --> 01:27:00.875
I know.

1195
01:27:03.006 --> 01:27:05.050
[Mary] Can you help me lie down?

1196
01:27:10.441 --> 01:27:12.006
[James] Sure.

1197
01:27:12.050 --> 01:27:14.919
[emotional music
playing on radio]

1198
01:27:28.528 --> 01:27:31.571
Okay. Okay. okay. okay.

1199
01:27:33.571 --> 01:27:34.875
[groans]

1200
01:27:43.745 --> 01:27:45.050
[silent sobs]

1201
01:27:51.658 --> 01:27:52.832
[glass breaks]

1202
01:27:54.962 --> 01:27:56.745
Come on.

1203
01:27:56.788 --> 01:27:58.658
There you go.

1204
01:27:58.701 --> 01:28:00.267
All right.

1205
01:28:06.788 --> 01:28:08.180
Just tell me
how I can help you.

1206
01:28:09.745 --> 01:28:11.398
You know.

1207
01:28:11.441 --> 01:28:12.788
[sniffles]

1208
01:28:14.441 --> 01:28:17.006
He's lived inside of me
for so long.

1209
01:28:18.441 --> 01:28:20.919
I don't want him there anymore.

1210
01:28:20.962 --> 01:28:22.050
I can't do that.

1211
01:28:22.093 --> 01:28:24.050
I want to be free.

1212
01:28:26.614 --> 01:28:28.224
Please. James.

1213
01:28:29.614 --> 01:28:30.919
Please.

1214
01:28:34.788 --> 01:28:36.745
Help me now.

1215
01:28:36.788 --> 01:28:38.180
[James sobbing]

1216
01:28:40.398 --> 01:28:42.180
[emotional music
playing on radio]

1217
01:28:53.528 --> 01:28:55.180
[crying]

1218
01:29:29.745 --> 01:29:31.354
[wings flapping]

1219
01:29:44.398 --> 01:29:46.398
[ground crumbling]

1220
01:30:02.093 --> 01:30:05.050
[ethereal music]

1221
01:30:29.658 --> 01:30:31.093
[ground crumbling]

1222
01:30:35.745 --> 01:30:39.441
[emotional music]

1223
01:30:52.919 --> 01:30:55.485
[wings flapping]

1224
01:31:10.485 --> 01:31:14.571
That day. I should've
died with you.

1225
01:31:14.614 --> 01:31:17.354
[wings flapping]

1226
01:31:33.832 --> 01:31:35.528
You forgave me.

1227
01:31:36.919 --> 01:31:39.050
but I could never
forgive myself.

1228
01:31:47.658 --> 01:31:50.311
I was so selfish. Mare.

1229
01:31:55.658 --> 01:31:57.441
Selfish and scared.

1230
01:32:17.919 --> 01:32:20.006
[car engine revving]

1231
01:32:23.311 --> 01:32:24.832
[water splashes]

1232
01:32:43.962 --> 01:32:45.398
[James] I'm ready now.

1233
01:32:50.137 --> 01:32:51.658
No matter what it takes.

1234
01:32:54.354 --> 01:32:56.137
No matter where it takes us.

1235
01:33:02.093 --> 01:33:03.093
This time...

1236
01:33:06.528 --> 01:33:08.137
I won't let go.

1237
01:33:21.788 --> 01:33:24.528
[Doctor] Mr. Sunderland?

1238
01:33:24.571 --> 01:33:25.919
Mr. Sunderland?

1239
01:33:25.962 --> 01:33:27.267
[truck honking]

1240
01:33:28.658 --> 01:33:30.398
[Doctor] Are you with us.
Mr. Sunderland?

1241
01:33:31.311 --> 01:33:32.398
[truck honking]

1242
01:33:32.441 --> 01:33:37.658
[tire screeching]

1243
01:33:40.832 --> 01:33:42.224
[breathing heavily] What?

1244
01:33:44.919 --> 01:33:46.267
[Mary] Oh. come on.

1245
01:33:46.311 --> 01:33:49.267
[running footsteps]

1246
01:33:49.311 --> 01:33:50.571
You've got to be kidding me.

1247
01:33:50.614 --> 01:33:53.398
[emotional music]

1248
01:33:58.137 --> 01:33:59.701
I'm so sorry.

1249
01:34:01.614 --> 01:34:02.832
Are you okay?

1250
01:34:02.875 --> 01:34:04.614
Yeah.
No. I'm fine. I'm fine.

1251
01:34:10.788 --> 01:34:12.180
Are you okay?

1252
01:34:13.311 --> 01:34:14.528
I think so.

1253
01:34:24.919 --> 01:34:26.050
It's okay. I got it.

1254
01:34:29.224 --> 01:34:30.485
The latch is broken.

1255
01:34:30.528 --> 01:34:31.528
How do you know that?

1256
01:34:31.571 --> 01:34:34.050
[distant honking]

1257
01:34:35.701 --> 01:34:37.050
Shit. that's my bus.

1258
01:34:38.441 --> 01:34:39.962
Hey. wait!

1259
01:34:44.006 --> 01:34:45.875
[suitcase latch snaps]

1260
01:34:45.919 --> 01:34:47.701
[horn honks]

1261
01:34:47.745 --> 01:34:49.962
Sorry. just...

1262
01:34:50.006 --> 01:34:51.788
[bus engine revs]

1263
01:34:54.006 --> 01:34:55.875
Where were you heading?

1264
01:34:55.919 --> 01:34:57.658
The next city.

1265
01:34:57.701 --> 01:35:00.354
Well. I just ruined your day.

1266
01:35:01.614 --> 01:35:04.224
Wouldn't be much of a gentleman
if I didn't try and help fix it.

1267
01:35:04.267 --> 01:35:06.050
A gentleman?

1268
01:35:06.093 --> 01:35:08.180
Didn't know
they made those anymore.

1269
01:35:08.224 --> 01:35:10.093
Gentleman named James.

1270
01:35:10.137 --> 01:35:12.745
-I'm--
-Mary.

1271
01:35:12.788 --> 01:35:14.267
I saw it on your case.

1272
01:35:15.919 --> 01:35:17.267
[chuckles]

1273
01:35:20.006 --> 01:35:21.224
[car hood shuts]

1274
01:35:24.745 --> 01:35:26.832
[wind blows]

1275
01:35:28.137 --> 01:35:29.962
You're a painter?

1276
01:35:31.441 --> 01:35:32.658
Yeah.

1277
01:35:35.919 --> 01:35:36.919
[car door closes]

1278
01:35:43.962 --> 01:35:45.224
What do you paint?

1279
01:35:51.919 --> 01:35:55.180
[car engine starts. revving]

1280
01:35:55.224 --> 01:35:58.093
[funky music playing]

1281
01:36:01.137 --> 01:36:02.571
[car tires screech]

1282
01:36:02.571 --> 01:36:32.571
<b>Subtitle | www.movieddl.me</b>

1283
01:36:39.614 --> 01:36:42.528
[static noise]

1284
01:36:49.050 --> 01:36:51.832
["Letter - from the Lost
Days" by Akira Yamaoka]

1285
01:37:17.528 --> 01:37:21.528
♪ A letter to my future self ♪

1286
01:37:21.571 --> 01:37:25.050
♪ Am I still happy? I began ♪

1287
01:37:25.093 --> 01:37:28.701
♪ Have I grown more pretty ♪

1288
01:37:28.745 --> 01:37:32.701
♪ Is Daddy still a good man? ♪

1289
01:37:32.745 --> 01:37:35.962
♪ Am I still friends
With Colleen ♪

1290
01:37:36.006 --> 01:37:40.093
♪ I'm sure that
I'm still laughing ♪

1291
01:37:40.137 --> 01:37:42.919
♪ Aren't I? ♪

1292
01:37:42.962 --> 01:37:45.485
♪ Aren't I? ♪

1293
01:37:54.224 --> 01:37:57.832
♪ Hey there to my future self ♪

1294
01:37:57.875 --> 01:38:01.745
♪ If you forget how to smile ♪

1295
01:38:01.788 --> 01:38:04.875
♪ I have this to tell you ♪

1296
01:38:04.919 --> 01:38:08.658
♪ Remember it once in a while ♪

1297
01:38:08.701 --> 01:38:12.528
♪ Ten years ago
Your past self ♪

1298
01:38:12.571 --> 01:38:15.919
♪ Prayed for your happiness ♪

1299
01:38:15.962 --> 01:38:21.788
♪ Please don't lose hope ♪

1300
01:38:23.180 --> 01:38:28.398
♪ Oh oh what a pair ♪

1301
01:38:28.441 --> 01:38:30.006
♪ Me and you ♪

1302
01:38:30.050 --> 01:38:34.050
♪ Put here to feel joy ♪

1303
01:38:34.093 --> 01:38:37.528
♪ Not be blue ♪

1304
01:38:37.571 --> 01:38:42.745
♪ Sad times and bad times ♪

1305
01:38:42.788 --> 01:38:45.093
♪ See them through ♪

1306
01:38:45.137 --> 01:38:51.788
♪ Soon we will know
If it's for real ♪

1307
01:38:51.832 --> 01:38:56.224
♪ What we both feel ♪

1308
01:38:59.571 --> 01:39:01.485
♪ Though I can't know for sure ♪

1309
01:39:01.528 --> 01:39:03.180
♪ How things worked out for us ♪

1310
01:39:04.875 --> 01:39:06.788
♪ So be happy ♪

1311
01:39:06.832 --> 01:39:08.788
♪ For me ♪

1312
01:39:08.832 --> 01:39:11.398
♪ For you ♪

1313
01:39:11.441 --> 01:39:15.441
♪ Feel joy ♪

1314
01:39:16.571 --> 01:39:19.398
[soft piano music]

1314
